title: "2.0: Building elements",
query: "PREFIX inst: <http://example.org/botTest#> PREFIX bot: <https://w3id.org/bot#> CONSTRUCT WHERE { ?a bot:adjacentElement ?b . ?a a ?aType . ?b a ?bType . }",
triples: "@prefix bot: <https://w3id.org/bot#> . @prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> . @prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> . @prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> . @prefix inst: <http://example.org/botTest#> . ############## # ABOX ############## inst:A bot:adjacentElement inst:B . inst:X bot:containsElement inst:Y . ############## # BOT SIMPLIFIED ############## bot:Zone a owl:Class . bot:Site a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf bot:Zone . bot:Building a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf bot:Zone . bot:Storey a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf	bot:Zone . bot:Space a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf	bot:Zone . bot:Element a owl:Class . bot:Interface a owl:Class . bot:containsZone a owl:ObjectProperty , owl:TransitiveProperty ; rdfs:domain	bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Zone . bot:adjacentZone a owl:ObjectProperty , owl:SymmetricProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Zone . bot:hasBuilding a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Building .	bot:hasStorey a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Storey . bot:hasSpace a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Space .	bot:adjacentElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Element . bot:containsElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Element ; owl:propertyChainAxiom ( bot:containsZone bot:containsElement ) . bot:hostsElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Element ; rdfs:range bot:Element . bot:interfaceOf a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Interface . [] a owl:AllDisjointClasses ; owl:members ( bot:Site bot:Element bot:Space bot:Storey bot:Building ) . [] a owl:AllDisjointClasses ; owl:members ( bot:Zone bot:Element ) . bot:Interface rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ; owl:onProperty bot:interfaceOf ; owl:cardinality 2 ] .",
description: "BOT describes a building element (`bot:Element`) as a *"Constituent of a construction entity with a characteristic technical function, form or position [12006-2, 3.4.7]"* The following two relationships can exist between a zone and an element according to the BOT definitions: * `<zone> bot:containsElement <element>` * `<zone> bot:adjacentElement <element>` BOT defines the domain of both of the two to be a `bot:Zone` and the range to be a `bot:Element`. #### ABox The ABox simply contains two triples stating that `inst:A` has a `bot:adjacentElement`, `inst:B` and that `inst:X bot:containsElement inst:Y`. #### TBox The TBox is the full BOT ontology without human readable labels and comments. ### Query The query asks for any ?a and ?b having the relationship `bot:adjacentElement` as a connection. ?a and ?b must further have a class specified. When performing the query without reasoning it will not return any result as inst:A and inst:B has no types explicitly assigned. The reasoner will infer these types based on the domain and range of `bot:adjacentElement` Try changing the query to ask for the `bot:containsElement` property instead to confirm that the same logigs are valid for this property.",
reasoning: true
},
{
title: "2.1: Building elements",
query: "PREFIX inst: <http://example.org/botTest#> PREFIX bot: <https://w3id.org/bot#> CONSTRUCT WHERE { ?site a bot:Site ; ?a ?b . }",
triples: "@prefix bot: <https://w3id.org/bot#> . @prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> . @prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> . @prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> . @prefix inst: <http://example.org/botTest#> . ############## # ABOX ############## inst:SiteA a bot:Site ; bot:hasBuilding inst:BuildingA . inst:BuildingA a bot:Building ; bot:hasStorey inst:Storey00 , inst:Storey01 . inst:Storey00 a bot:Storey ; bot:hasSpace inst:SpaceA , inst:SpaceB . inst:Storey01 a bot:Storey ; bot:hasSpace inst:SpaceC , inst:SpaceD . inst:SpaceA a bot:Space ; bot:adjacentElement inst:Wall ; bot:containsElement inst:Chair1 , inst:Chair2 , inst:Chair3 , inst:Chair4 . inst:SpaceB a bot:Space . inst:SpaceC a bot:Space . inst:SpaceD a bot:Space . inst:Chair1 a bot:Element. inst:Chair2 a bot:Element . inst:Chair3 a bot:Element . inst:Chair4 a bot:Element . inst:Wall a bot:Element . ############## # BOT SIMPLIFIED ############## bot:Zone a owl:Class . bot:Site a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf bot:Zone . bot:Building a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf bot:Zone . bot:Storey a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf	bot:Zone . bot:Space a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf	bot:Zone . bot:Element a owl:Class . bot:Interface a owl:Class . bot:containsZone a owl:ObjectProperty , owl:TransitiveProperty ; rdfs:domain	bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Zone . bot:adjacentZone a owl:ObjectProperty , owl:SymmetricProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Zone . bot:hasBuilding a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Building .	bot:hasStorey a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Storey . bot:hasSpace a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:subPropertyOf bot:containsZone ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Space .	bot:adjacentElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Element . bot:containsElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Zone ; rdfs:range bot:Element ; owl:propertyChainAxiom ( bot:containsZone bot:containsElement ) . bot:hostsElement a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Element ; rdfs:range bot:Element . bot:interfaceOf a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:domain bot:Interface . [] a owl:AllDisjointClasses ; owl:members ( bot:Site bot:Element bot:Space bot:Storey bot:Building ) . [] a owl:AllDisjointClasses ; owl:members ( bot:Zone bot:Element ) . bot:Interface rdfs:subClassOf [ a owl:Restriction ; owl:onProperty bot:interfaceOf ; owl:cardinality 2 ] .",
description: "BOT has a property chain axiom stating that if `<A> bot:containsZone <B>` AND `<B> bot:containsElement <C>` THEN `<A> containsElement <C>`. #### ABox Same as tab 1.0 but with the following additions: * `inst:SpaceA` contains 4 chairs: `inst:Chair1`, `inst:Chair2`, `inst:Chair3` and `inst:Chair4` * `inst:SpaceA` has an adjacent element, `inst:Wall` ### Query The query is the same as in tab 1.1, but the elements contained in the space contained at the storey contained in the building contained at the site are also indirectly contained in the site (because of the axiom explained above). The site will hence also contain the four chairs contained in `inst:SpaceA`.",
